As Australia makes plans to gradually lift its coronavirus lockdown, we look at what the rest of the world is doingThe exit strategy: how countries around the world are preparing for life after Covid-19Australia has a road out of its coronavirus lockdown, long and winding though it may be.
On Monday, Ardern’s cabinet will meet to discuss winding back its lockdown measures, from “level four” to “level three”.
Early childhood centres and schools will reopen for students up to year 10 under level three, but attendance would remain voluntary.
Hairdressers will also be allowed to reopen on the same day if they undertake precautions to guarantee hygiene for customers and staff.
Austria has allowed small shops, hardware and gardening shops to reopen, along with public parks (with strict distancing rules and masks).